        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Marietta O.</placeName>
                <date>Friday March 5, 1858</date>.</p>
            <p>Rev. &amp; Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>inclose</sic> six dollars to you,<lb/> hoping it will reach
                you safely. As I now<lb/> have a family to support, and serve a congrega=<lb/>tion
                who are far back in supporting me, and am<lb/> pressed for funds, I feel as if I
                must say to you<lb/> that I feel unable to take the “Occident” any<lb/> longer. You
                will please therefore discontinue<lb/> it. Probably in better circumstances I
                will<lb/> take it again.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is pleasant to reflect on the politeness<lb/> which we have
                maintained towards each other, though<lb/> occupying adverse standpoints. Am always
                pleased<lb/> to hear from you.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I try to watch the development of the des=<lb/>tiny of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> in these <placeName>U. S.</placeName> with
                great<lb/> interest and sincere prayer.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours most respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. R. Miller</persName>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
